sub_title: Accelerate potato breeding utilizing biological and genomic data research
summary:
I am a curious, pro-active and sociable bioinformatics researcher at seed potato breeder HZPC Holland BV. In this job I can fully indulge my interests in biology and informatics. I research the underlaying genetics of several traits in potato.

Besides work I give my heart as a volunteer within the staff association and my volleyball club.

Since my birth I have always been curious in how things work, especially in engineering and life. I studied biotechnology to get a technical understanding on how an organism works on the molecular level. My bioinformatics minor helped me combining my interest in biology and computers and to be able to perform in a job that perfectly fits my curiousities. Exploring the workings of life is an amazing puzzle!
